discovery_rule.params:
select '{"data":['
    , (
        select STUFF((
                    select ',' + '{"{#DBNAME}":"' + [Name] + '"}'
                    from master..sysdatabases
                    order by [Name]
                    for xml PATH('')
                    ), 1, 1, '')
        )
    , ']}'
for xml PATH('')

select replace((
            select '{"data":['
                , (
                    select STUFF((
                                select ',' + '{"{#JOBNAME}":"' + (
                                        case 
                                            when [Name] like '%\%'
                                                then REPLACE([Name], '\', '\\')
                                            else [Name]
                                            end
                                        ) + '"}'
                                from msdb..sysjobs
                                where enabled = 1
                                order by [Name]
                                for xml PATH('')
                                ), 1, 1, '')
                    )
                , ']}'
            for xml PATH('')
            ), char(13) + char(10), '')

discovery_rule.description:
Discovery of Jobs as defined in global regular expression "MSSQL Jobs for discovery".

For manual select:

select '{"data":[
     {"{#JOBNAME}":"JobName1"}
    ,{"{#JOBNAME}":"JobName2"}
    ,{"{#JOBNAME}":"JobName3"}
]}
'
